The paper deals with variational inference, which is a popular technique in machine learning and statistics for approximating complex posterior distributions. The paper also uses Monte Carlo estimation, which is a common tool in many areas of computer science. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also discusses the use of divergence measures, which are commonly used in information theory and statistics, suggesting that cs.ST (Statistics) and cs.IT (Information Theory) are also possible sub-categories.
